definition: to sell/to betray/to spare no effort/to show off or flaunt

sentences.english: The peach pies and chocolate Mousse cakes are nearly finished.
sentences.chinese: 桃馅饼和巧克力慕斯蛋糕也接近卖完。

sentences.english: The vendor can turn his stock every day.
sentences.chinese: 小贩每天都能把进的货卖完。

sentences.english: I saw the other day when Chelsea played against Leverkusen - it was not a sell-out.
sentences.chinese: 就在切尔西对阵勒沃库森的时候，球票就没有卖完。

sentences.english: We're packed out and again chiefly to young people.
sentences.chinese: 我们的票卖完了，主要又是卖给年轻人的。

sentences.english: Show that does well in the tryouts in the provinces is likely to be sold out weeks in advance .
sentences.chinese: 在外埠试演成功的戏大概几个星期以前票就卖完了。

sentences.english: I'm sorry, we're fresh out of popcorn.
Sorry, sleepers are all sold out. We have only soft seats left.
sentences.chinese: 对不起，卧铺票已经卖完了，只有软座。

sentences.english: Meat quickly sold, the elderly victoriously home.
sentences.chinese: 肉很快就卖完了，老人胜利地回家。

sentences.english: But when we returned from looking into other stalls, we found they'd all been sold.
sentences.chinese: 但是等我们从市场上返回时竟然发现已经卖完了。

sentences.english: I had no grab one at the store before they sold out.
sentences.chinese: 我得在他们卖完之前，在书店里抓一本。

sentences.english: We are amazed at how fast these went ourselves.
sentences.chinese: 我们惊讶地发现在这么短的时间卖完。

sentences.english: Trouble started when they ran out of dolls.
sentences.chinese: 当洋娃娃卖完的时候麻烦就开始了。

sentences.english: We should have applied for block seating before it is sold out.
sentences.chinese: 我们当时在门票卖完前应该申请团体座位才对。

sentences.english: How'd you get tickets to this concert? I thought it was sold-out.
sentences.chinese: 你怎么拿到演唱会的票啊？我还以为都卖完了咧。

sentences.english: I am sorry. The flight is fully booked for the 20th.
sentences.chinese: 很抱歉，20日的机票全卖完了。
